==Classical Nahuatl==
===Other spellings===
*[[ypalhnemoani]]
*[[Ipal-Nemohuani]]
===Etymology===
''[[ipal]]'' "by his/her/its/their grace" + ''[[nemohuani]]'' "everyone habitually lives", from ''[[nemohua]]'' "everyone lives", from ''[[nemi]]'' "he/she/it/they live"
===Noun===
'''īpalnemohuani'''

# One by whose grace we live.
===Usage note===
Used to describe various gods, including [[Titlacahuan-Tezcatlipoca]], [[Quetzalcoatl]], and the Christian [[God]].
